two weeks off social media not as if its some sort of accomplishment but I FEEL so reconnected to myself. took a lot of time to reflect on my life and experience during revival retreat. Feeling very uplifted and optimistic as well as grateful for meeting such amazing people and being able to connect to myself, nature, and inner strength and purpose while being able to be fully present in the moment. Life can get so chaotic, As someone who’s struggled with anxiety I find it’s immensely important to to take care of your mental health and well being above all else. I found that disconnecting for a period was the key to connecting to myself more fully. Been really focusing on what’s most important to me in my life and radiating those things ✨🧬 🧠🪄Feeling so grounded and grateful for these recent experiences.

may is mental health awareness month and sometimes It's tough to share what's real, what's vulnerable and what makes you uncomfortable. one of the reasons we're all exhausted is because we're always masking. Putting on a facade, trying to be easy or not a be too much for others. For a long time I fell victim to this and the best thing I ever did for my mental health was stopped apologizing for it. By age 40, about 50% of the population will have or have had a mental illness. one of the most powerful ways to create change is to share and empathize. when we give others the opportunity to share their own struggles with mental health we create a safe and open space for connection and understanding and that has been one of the most profound things in feeling like i’m not alone in this. The second picture is a day where I felt the weight of the world so intensely and consumed by anxiety and remember thinking I need to take a picture to remember this to emphasize i can come out of these feelings and they don’t last forever. Those days come and that’s OK. Mental Health affects every single aspect of your life and is so important to understand yourself and the things that bring you peace and make you feel like your most authentic self.  And for those who might not relate, this window of education and sharing we provide can give them a better understanding and clear up any misconceptions regarding mental illness. Everything is not what it seems. Social media can be the biggest facade and not a real depiction of people’s daily struggles or what they’re going through. Taking the time to check in on your friends and have candid conversations can be life changing. the simple act of actively listening to someone without judgment can mean more than you’d ever know. above all someone will always remember how you made them feel in a time of needing connection.

Last October I got Certified in becoming a professional life coach. Coming from a family of mental health professionals and always having had exposure to watching people around me help others from a  young age. Being a life coach is so meaningful to me and ultimately part of my life trajectory. 

 Having had dealt with an array of my own challenges and grief / mental health struggles- being present for someone in any capacity, connecting is one of my greatest passions in this life, and ultimately gives me the most peace within myself. 

I’ve become obsessed with self help, self growth, and immersing myself into studying humans and why we operate the way we do. Rewriting Patterns, Self Analytics as well as tapping into our greatest potential is truly my passion. I’ve been doing this behind the scenes for some time and wanted to wait to post until it felt “perfect”, but told myself there’s never a “perfect” time for anything. The perfect time is always now and literally everyone starts somewhere. 

Noetic is A kind of Metarational awareness or insight like intuition but more conscious and grounded in reason. It refers to "inner knowing," a kind of intuitive consciousness, or direct and immediate access to knowledge beyond what is available to our normal senses or the power of reason and felt immediately right as a name for my business. Along with life coaching being certified in reiki level 1+2 is something that’s helped me feel more centered and grounded within myself. The ultimate mind + body connection duo. 

I am so excited to continue this passion of mine and continue to learn new dynamics and implementing knowledge and connection. This is just the beginning of so much to come. 

In honor of Mother’s day I dedicate this to my mom and her many acts of service to others and the countless people she helped throughout her life.  @noeticcoaching
